quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
46,29,"And call to mind when We sent to you a party of the jinn that they may listen to the Qur'an. {1} When they reached the place (where you were reciting the Qur'an), they said to one another: “Be silent (and listen).” And when the recitation ended, they went back to their people as warners.",footnotes:1:The traditions that have been related from Abdullah bin Masud
46,30,"They said: “Our people, We have heard a Scripture revealed after Moses, verifying the Scriptures revealed before it; it guides to the Truth and to the Straight Way. {1}",footnotes:1:This shows that these jinns had already had faith in the Prophet Moses (peace be upon him) and in the divine Books. After hearing the Quran they felt that it gave the same teachings as the former Prophets had been preaching. Therefore
46,31,"Our people, respond to the call of him who calls you to Allah and believe in him. Allah will forgive your sins and will protect you from a grievous chastisement.” {1}",footnotes:1:Authentic traditions show that after this several deputations of the jinns visited the Prophet (peace be upon him)
46,32,"And {1} he who does not respond to the one who calls to Allah will not be able to frustrate Him on earth, nor will they have anyone to protect them from Allah. Such people are in manifest error.",footnotes:1:This sentence might also be a part of the saying of the jinns
46,33,"Do they not see that Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth � and creating them did not wear Him out � has the power to bring the dead back to life? Why not! He certainly has the power over everything."
46,34,"On the Day when the unbelievers will be brought within sight of the Fire, they will be asked: “Is this not the Truth?” and they will answer “Yes, by Our Lord (this is the Truth).” Allah will say: “Then suffer the chastisement as a requital for your disbelieving.”"
46,35,"So bear with patience, (O Prophet), even as the Messengers endowed with firmness of resolve {1} (before you) bore with patience, and do not be hasty in their regard. The Day when they see what they had been warned against they will feel as though they had remained in the world no more than an hour of a day. (The Truth has been conveyed.) Will any, then, suffer perdition except those who disobey?",footnotes:1:That is
